        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 2:03PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 203 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Julian, or 8 miles northeast of Madison, moving east at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Montgomery, Chesapeake, Belle, Cedar Grove, East Bank, Glasgow,
Pratt, Burnwell, Handley, Seth, Leewood, Dawes, Ashford, Sharon,
Eskdale, and Racine.

This includes West Virginia Turnpike between mile markers 67 and 87.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
